Paper: hep-th/9205023

Date: 1992-05-12

Title: Stability Analysis of a Stringy Black Hole

Authors: Rue-Ron Hsu, Green Huang , Wei-Fu Lin, and Chin-Rong Lee

Comments: 7 pages

Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 10 (1993) 505-508

We investigate the stability of charged black holes in two-dimensionalheterotic string theories that were recently discussed by McGuidan, Nappi andYost. In the framework of small time-dependent perturbation, we find that theseblack holes are linearly stable.